**One extra recommendation:** For a **Spring Boot microservice audit**, I would add a **9th category called "Spring-specific practices"** because Spring applications have many framework-specific anti-patterns that generic architecture audits miss (`@Transactional`, `@Async`, bean scopes, JPA fetch types, configuration properties, actuator usage, etc.). That's usually where the most valuable findings are.
